OL,3,C'I constantly look over my shoulder' -
OL,4,Cyoung rape victim sees attacker jailed
OL,6,FThe rape victim said in her victim
OL,7,Fpersonal statement: "Generally day to
OL,8,Fday, I constantly feel I am looking
OL,9,Fover my shoulder.
OL,11,F"I know he is in prison but if I see
OL,12,Fanyone who looks like him I freak out
OL,13,Fand have to stop and tell myself it
OL,14,Fcouldn't be him as he is in prison.
OL,16,F"But it still reinvigorates the memory
OL,17,Fof what he did."
OL,19,FShe said she used to be outgoing but
OL,20,Fnow would much rather stay at home
OL,21,Fbecause that makes her feel safer.
